VALID.E2BE2B


Title: The Coming of the Bots: The Future of the Human Workforce




Biography


Santanu is the founding CEO and MD at TalentSprint, IndiaE2s leading
 Youth
Career Accelerator. TalentSprint offers a digitally intelligent platform
that empowers every young person to pursue an exciting career of their
choice.


The platform seeks to enable ONE MILLION youth in sectors such as
Information Technology, Banking and Financial Services, and Education by
2020. TalentSprint has won fifteen national and international awards till
date and raised venture capital from Nexus Ventures and NSDC.


From 20032008, Santanu worked at Virtusa Corporation as Senior Vice
President for Global Delivery Operations and the Head of Indian Operations.
From 19992003, Santanu worked in Boston as Chief Technology Officer of
Viveca and Openpages, both venturebacked technology firms. He began his
career as a Research Scientist at the famed IBM T.J. Watson Research Center
in Yorktown Heights, New York.


Santanu has a B.Tech. in Computer Science from IIT Madras and a Ph.D. in
Software Engineering from the University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, where his
academic performance earned him the prestigious Rackham Doctoral
Fellowship, the IBM Canada Fellowship, and the LaCroute Fellowship. He is
an author or coauthor on 20 international technology papers and 2 United
States patents.


He is a member of the Young Presidents Organization (YPO), a Distinguished
Fellow of IDRBT (set up by RBI), a Technology Advisor to the National
Payments Corporation of India (NPCI), and a Visiting Professor at IIT
Hyderabad. He is a frequent speaker at conferences and writes often for
mainstream and business media.


With regards....

